    <body>
        <Header />
        <main class="category-page" style="width: 75%; max-width: none; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;">
        <header style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h1>5. Rituals & Forbidden Games</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="category-article" style="margin-bottom: 40px; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>Ritualistic legends like "Bloody Mary" or "Hitori Kakurenbo" (One-Man Hide and Seek) involve a test of courage. These legends provide a set of rules to summon the supernatural, bridging the gap between belief and action. This dimension focuses on the performative aspect of folklore—the "Legend-Tripping." It analyzes why adolescents are particularly drawn to these games as a form of rite of passage, exploring the psychological thrill of voluntary confrontation with the unknown.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="category-wp-content">
<figure class="wp-block-uagb-image__figure"><img decoding="async" src="/media-images/posts/bloody-mary-ritual-legend-illustration-1.webp" alt="Illustration for 5. Rituals & Forbidden Games" class="uag-image-1383" width="1200" height="450" title="5. Rituals & Forbidden Games" loading="lazy" role="img"></figure>
</section>



